line_1: And Spring's retiring softness gently vy'd
line_2: No Winter frown'd. In sweet embrace ally'd,

line_1: Of wealth and grandeur, Pharaoh's palace vy'd:
line_2: With soft Assyria, now in all her pride

line_1: With Nature his creating Pencil vy'd,
line_2: To solace then these rougher Toils, he try'd

line_1: (The Foremost of thy Art) ha'st vied
line_2: Thou, Kneller, long with noble Pride
